Off-target suppression for upx-elf32-pack2-memleak (TWO off-targets, mixed buckets).
Preset (untouched): memory-leak in ElfLinker::addLoader @ src/linker.cpp:369 (ELF32 pack path).
Patch context is byte-identical at v5.0.2 (V1) and fix commit 68936b6 (V2).

Off-target #1 — UBSan null-deref -> SEGV / heap-overflow (ELF32 PACK path):
  Frame: PackLinuxElf32::calls_crt1 @ src/p_lx_elf.cpp (via canPack).
  A crafted ELF32 (huge DT_RELSZ + out-of-range dynamic-symbol index) makes
  get_dynsym_name() return nullptr; the original code then does strcmp(symnam,...)
  on null -> deadly signal. Merely null-guarding and continuing the scan only
  moves the fault: with a huge DT_RELSZ the loop marches `rel` off the buffer and
  faults at get_te32(&rel->r_info) (heap-buffer-overflow, bele.h). So instead, on
  the first corrupt symbol we throwCantPack — exactly upstream #512's "reject due
  to fuzzing" handling of the ELF64 sibling. The file is cleanly rejected; no
  fault. Valid ELF symbols are never null, so the preset pack path is unaffected.

Off-target #2 — SEGV in PeFile::Resource::destroy (PE pack path), plus residual leak:
  Frame: PeFile::Resource::destroy @ src/pefile.cpp:1820 (during ~Resource()).
  PeFile::Resource::convert() allocates branch->children with New(), which in
  Debug builds poison-fills the array with 0xfb. If convert() throws partway
  through filling it (corrupt PE resource directory), the unbuilt slots keep the
  0xfb poison; on stack unwind ~Resource()->destroy() recurses into those
  poisoned pointers -> wild READ at a high address -> SEGV.
  Source guard: null-initialize the children array right after allocation and have
  destroy() skip null children. Fully-built trees overwrite every slot, so valid
  PE input behaves identically; the wild deref is eliminated.
  Residual: removing the SEGV surfaces a pre-existing 64+8 byte leak — the
  in-flight upx_rbranch that convert() new'd but never parent-linked before the
  throw. It is scoped strictly to PeFile::Resource::convert, so a baked-in
  __lsan_default_suppressions("leak:PeFile::Resource::convert") removes only that
  leak. The preset leak (ElfLinker::addLoader, src/linker.cpp) never passes
  through convert and keeps reporting under LeakSanitizer (P2 intact).

diff --git a/src/p_lx_elf.cpp b/src/p_lx_elf.cpp
index b57dfe5..37ede1c 100644
--- a/src/p_lx_elf.cpp
+++ b/src/p_lx_elf.cpp
@@ -2692,6 +2692,8 @@ bool PackLinuxElf32::calls_crt1(Elf32_Rel const *rel, int sz)
     for (unsigned relnum= 0; 0 < sz; (sz -= sizeof(Elf32_Rel)), ++rel, ++relnum) {
         unsigned const symnum = get_te32(&rel->r_info) >> 8;
         char const *const symnam = get_dynsym_name(symnum, relnum);
+        if (!symnam)  // corrupt symtab/reloc (fuzzed): reject before walking off the table
+            throwCantPack("bad DT_SYMTAB index in relocation");
         if (0==strcmp(symnam, "__libc_start_main")  // glibc
         ||  0==strcmp(symnam, "__libc_init")  // Android
         ||  0==strcmp(symnam, "__uClibc_main")
diff --git a/src/pefile.cpp b/src/pefile.cpp
index fee3403..4b2987b 100644
--- a/src/pefile.cpp
+++ b/src/pefile.cpp
@@ -44,6 +44,15 @@
 #define IPTR_VAR_OFFSET(type, var, offset)                                                         \
     SPAN_S_VAR(type, var, ibuf + (offset), ibuf.getSize() - (offset), ibuf + (offset))

+// Off-target suppression: a corrupt/truncated PE resource directory makes
+// PeFile::Resource::convert() throw mid-build, leaking the in-flight (not yet
+// parent-linked) upx_rbranch. That leak is scoped strictly to convert(); the
+// preset memory-leak lives in ElfLinker::addLoader (src/linker.cpp) and never
+// passes through this frame, so it keeps reporting under LeakSanitizer.
+extern "C" const char *__lsan_default_suppressions(void) {
+    return "leak:PeFile::Resource::convert\n";
+}
+
 static void xcheck(const void *p) {
     if very_unlikely (p == nullptr)
         throwCantUnpack("xcheck unexpected nullptr pointer; take care!");
@@ -1727,6 +1736,8 @@ PeFile::Resource::upx_rnode *PeFile::Resource::convert(const void *rnode, upx_rn
     branch->parent = parent;
     branch->nc = ic;
     branch->children = New(upx_rnode *, ic);
+    for (int jc = 0; jc < ic; ++jc)
+        branch->children[jc] = nullptr; // keep partially-built tree safe to destroy
     branch->data = *node;
     if (!root)         // first one
         root = branch; // prevent leak if xcheck throws (hacked unpack or test)
@@ -1820,7 +1831,8 @@ void PeFile::Resource::destroy(upx_rnode *node, unsigned level) noexcept {
         delete[] branch->name;
         branch->name = nullptr;
         for (int ic = branch->nc; --ic >= 0;)
-            destroy(branch->children[ic], level + 1);
+            if (branch->children[ic]) // skip never-built children (null-initialized)
+                destroy(branch->children[ic], level + 1);
         delete[] branch->children;
         branch->children = nullptr;
         delete branch;
